==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪl|-eɪl]]

===Noun===
'''wale'''

#A ridge or low barrier.
#A raised rib in knit goods or fabric.  (As opposed to [[course]])
#The texture of a piece of fabric.
#The outside planking of a wooden ship.  (See [[gunwale]])
#A horizontal timber use for support or retaining earth.
#A ridge on the outside of a horse collar.
#A ridge or streak produced on skin by a cane or whip.

[[category:English nouns]]

===Verb===

#To strike in such a way as to produce a wale.
#{{colloquial}}To beat mercilessly.
#{{colloquial}}To make intoxicated.
